Traffic In\ntltute.\nihlna, the document said:\n\u201cFor the purpose of strengthening\nihlna\u2019s power of resistance against\napanese aggression, any arrange\nlent should provide for extension\nf aid to China by the partlclpat\nig powers, principally In the mat*\nsr of arms, war materials and\nnanclal help.\u201d\nNEW DEAL OPENS\nUP FOR BRAZIL\nRio De Janeiro, Brazil, Nov. 15\u2014\n(UP)\u2014President Oetulio Vargas\noffered Brazil a \"New Deal\u201d today\nby planning a series of economlo\nand Industrial measures that pos\nsibly may Include creation of a new\ncentral bank, a new defense pro\ngram and consideration of foreign\ndebts. Vargas said that the United\nStates merited special consideration\nbut did not specify whether or not\nhe intended eventually to seek\nUnited States aid In drawing up a\nnew plan for paying foreign debts.\nVargas contemplated large pur\nchases of railroad equipment\nabroad In the near future. The In\ndustrial program would welcome\nthe aid of foreign capital, he added.\nThe work of reforming the coun\ntry\u2019s credit system already was\nstarted and was expected to be\ncompleted within a sort time. Var\ngas Indicated that the campaign\nagainst Communism would be\nstrengthened. A new and perma\nnent defense organization also will\nbe built up, Vargas Indicated. The\nminister of marine, meanwhile, an\nnounced that the keel of a new\nmine vessel would be laid down\nshortly and that plans for the\nconstruction of other warships also\nwould be discussed soon.\nMOTHER OF PLAYER DIES\nBoston, Nov. 16 (U.P.)\nFuneral services will be held to\nmorrow for Senora Marla Sanroma,\n76, mother of Jesus Marla Sanroma,\nsoloist and official pianist of Boston\nSymphony orchestra. She died Sat\nurday after an Illness that started\nwith the death of her husband last\nAugust.\nHer marriage to Don Jose Maria\nSanroma Y. Ripoll, then In Portu\ngal, was by proxy under a 16th\ncentury Iberian law.\nMore new automobiles are seen In\nTurkey than a year ago.